{"cwd": "/tmp/cch-sandboxes/20260703T163334/websearch-tool", "duration_ms": 10010, "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "prompt_id": "3c14bd68-ee5c-477a-a007-5d9e8239d9bb", "session_id": "<SESSION_ID>", "tool_input": {"query": "claude code hooks"}, "tool_name": "WebSearch", "tool_response": {"durationSeconds": 10.011381259999995, "query": "claude code hooks", "results": [{"content": [{"title": "Hooks reference - Claude Code Docs", "url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks"}, {"title": "GitHub - disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery: Master Claude Code Hooks · GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery"}, {"title": "Claude Code hooks explained: the missing layer between prompts and production", "url": "https://joseparreogarcia.substack.com/p/claude-code-hooks-explained-the-missing"}, {"title": "GitHub - karanb192/claude-code-hooks: 🪝 A growing collection of useful Claude Code hooks. Copy, paste, customize.", "url": "https://github.com/karanb192/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Complete Guide to All 12 Lifecycle Events", "url": "https://claudefa.st/blog/tools/hooks/hooks-guide"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Automate Your AI Coding Workflow", "url": "https://www.ksred.com/claude-code-hooks-a-complete-guide-to-automating-your-ai-coding-workflow/"}, {"title": "Steering Claude Code: skills, hooks, subagents and more | Claude by Anthropic", "url": "https://claude.com/blog/steering-claude-code-skills-hooks-rules-subagents-and-more"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks Complete Guide — Automate and Enforce Rules Reliably - SmartScope", "url": "https://smartscope.blog/en/generative-ai/claude/claude-code-hooks-guide/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: The Feature You’re Ignoring While Babysitting Your AI | by Lakshmi Narasimhan | Medium", "url": "https://medium.com/@lakshminp/claude-code-hooks-the-feature-youre-ignoring-while-babysitting-your-ai-789d39b46f6c"}], "tool_use_id": "srvtoolu_01J11t9W4sfvFGp37btVitzr"}, "Based on the search results, here's what Claude Code hooks are:\n\n## Overview\n\nHooks are user-defined shell commands, HTTP endpoints, or LLM prompts that execute automatically at specific points in Claude Code's lifecycle. Hooks fire at specific points during a Claude Code session.\n\n## How They Work\n\nWhen an event fires and a matcher matches, Claude Code passes JSON context about the event to your hook handler. A hook starts with an event, can optionally be narrowed with a matcher, receives structured input from Claude Code, and then executes one or more handlers.\n\n## Types of Hooks\n\nThere are several types of hooks: command, HTTP, mcp_tool, prompt, and agent. These allow you to:\n\n- Run a shell command, where your script receives the event's JSON input on stdin and communicates results back through exit codes and stdout\n- Send the event's JSON input as an HTTP POST request to a URL, with the endpoint communicating results back through the response body\n- Send a prompt to a Claude model for single-turn evaluation, with the model returning a yes/no decision as JSON\n\n## Key Difference from Prompts\n\nUnlike prompt instructions, which are requests that Claude may interpret flexibly, hooks execute the same way every time. The critical difference from prompt-based rules is that hooks are guaranteed to execute.\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\n- Every time Claude Code writes or edits a file, a PostToolUse hook can run your formatter automatically, avoiding reviewing diffs full of formatting inconsistencies\n- Rather than giving Claude Code blanket permission and hoping for the best, you set up a PreToolUse hook that inspects every bash command before it runs\n- The Stop event fires whenever Claude finishes responding, and if your hook returns a blocking signal, Claude is forced to keep working, combining this with a prompt hook where a separate model evaluates whether all requested tasks were completed"], "searchCount": 1}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_017jTVPkYHn6V5yBcoF5YLZK", "transcript_path": "<TRANSCRIPT_PATH>"}
